This paper involves the development of a conversational search agent using reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of virtual users to model human behavior also involves machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the focus on user engagement and interaction suggests a potential overlap with human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
